                                    Wellington Management Singapore is an active manager performs in-house research to invest in a range of equity, fixed-income and multi-asset approaches across markets, capitalizations and styles.The firm follows a Global Value approach to invest in the stocks of financially sound but out-of-favor companies that provide above-average total return potential and generally sell at below-average price/earnings multiples. They make investment decisions based on in-house fundamental research and security valuations.Wellington Management Singapore utilizes their multi-disciplinary research to integrate quantitative and fundamental fixed-income, currency, equity and commodity analysis from around the world.  Their diversified approach seeks to minimize portfolio volatility. They employ proprietary models and external systems to manage risk and construct portfolios based on clients'' risk tolerance and return objectives.The firm develops multi-asset client solutions, combining top-down asset allocation with bottom-up security selection and complements investment programs with a range of alternative approaches, investing in metals, agriculture, climate change, emerging markets equity and debt.                                




